{"id":8662,"date":"2018-02-19T13:23:46","date_gmt":"2018-02-19T12:23:46","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/?p=8662"},"modified":"2018-02-19T14:02:55","modified_gmt":"2018-02-19T13:02:55","slug":"keepin-it-green-glastonbury-2017","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/keepin-it-green-glastonbury-2017\/","title":{"rendered":"Keepin\u2019 it green \u2013 Glastonbury 2017"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>We love catering for all kinds of events, but our sweet spot is feeding the crew and artists backstage at all the greatest music festivals in the UK. Many of the crew chose to eat in the Radish marquee, but we also offer take out \u2013 our consumables are all <strong>environmentally friendly<\/strong> and <strong>biodegradable<\/strong> and we wouldn\u2019t have it any other way.<!--more--><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\" wp-image-6143 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/DSC008231-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"268\" height=\"178\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/DSC008231-300x199.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/DSC008231-600x399.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/DSC008231-436x290.jpg 436w, https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/DSC008231.jpg 640w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 268px) 100vw, 268px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The festival we\u2019ve been doing the longest is Glastonbury, and this year we had three super kitchens on site to feed our delicious grub to the hungry folks of Glasto.\u00a0Over four weeks we served up nearly 14,000 meals &#8211; breakfast, lunch and dinner. A combination of healthy salads, and hearty fry ups, naughty chocolate brownies, and of course the famous Red Radish Sunday roast were just some of the menu items that tickled peoples taste buds. We pride ourselves on our fresh, quality and varied food and despite the \u2018great\u2019 British weather our nearly 50 strong team kept everyone smiling and well fed.<\/p>\n<p>Over at Radish HQ\u00a0we have been working hard to reduce our carbon footprint and we encourage both our staff and clients to reduce, reuse, recycle. Luckily the team at Glastonb<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-6161 alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/DSC008681-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"112\" height=\"169\" \/>ury have this motto at their core so it\u2019s always a pleasure to work with them. At the festival in 2017 we only used gorgeous local produce sourced from the on-site wholesale market made up of community suppliers. Not only did it taste amazing but it reduced the number of food miles, and contributed to the local economy.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>We love catering for all kinds of events, but our sweet spot is feeding the crew and artists backstage at all the greatest music festivals in the UK. Many of&#8230; <a class=\"more-link\" href=\"https:\/\/www.red-radish.com\/keepin-it-green-glastonbury-2017\/\"><span class=\"button button-outline button-dark\" style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> read more <i class=\"fa fa-long-arrow-right\"><\/i><\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":8665,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[242,240,27,12,18,244,241,243,239],"tags":[41,249,246,250,248,247,245],"class_list":["post-8662","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-eco-friendly","category-environmentally-friendly","category-festivals","category-food","category-great-suppliers","category-green","category-recycling","category-responsible","category-sustainability","tag-blog","tag-catering","tag-eco-friendly","tag-festivals","tag-green","tag-recycling","tag-sustainability"],"yoast_head":"<